The article discusses a meeting between leaders of NATO Allies to discuss their commitment to collective defense and Transatlantic security. The President emphasizes that NATO stands for freedom and democracy, particularly in the face of threats from President Putin. The United States is committed to defending every inch of NATO territory and has ordered the deployment of additional forces to Europe to support Allies. NATO's defensive plans and the NATO Response Force are being activated, and Allies are deploying additional land, air, and maritime forces to strengthen the collective posture. Close partners such as Sweden, Finland, and the European Union also joined the meeting. The President states that NATO remains united and resolute, and the Open Door policy will continue for European states that share NATO's values. The President also spoke with President Zelenskyy of Ukraine, commending the bravery of the Ukrainian people and pledging ongoing support from the United States.